<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="identification-n">identification <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /aɪˌdentɪfɪ'keɪʃn/    美 /aɪˌdentɪfɪ'keɪʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>识别；鉴定；确认</strong></h4>
<p>when you recognize sth or discover exactly what it is：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Each product in the supermarket has an <strong>identification number</strong>.
超市里的每件产品都有一个识别码。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Each unit leader needed a flag, or colour, to be easily seen for identification during a battle.
战斗中，每个队长都需要一面旗子或一种颜色，容易看到，易于识别。</p><footer>译林⑨ – 3</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-id">2.★ <strong>[缩写为ID] 身份证明 (文件) ：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We are all asked to show some identification — an identity card or a passport — before boarding the plane. 
登机前，我们都需要出示身份证明，如身份证或护照。</p></div></div>